Class OneBoxResults

java.lang.Object
  com.google.enterprise.sdk.onebox.OneBoxResults
All Implemented Interfaces:
IOneBoxResults
public class OneBoxResults
extends java.lang.Object
implements IOneBoxResults

Class encapsulating a response result set from a call to a OneBox provider.

OneBox clients expect an XML response that adhere's to Google's Schema. This class, along with ModuleResult and Field, hides those details by providing an API for conveniently building a result set. The serialize() method serializes the class' current state as a valid OneBox for Enterprise XML response.

See Also:
ModuleResult, Field

Method Detail

setFailure

public void setFailure(FailureCode failureCode,
                       java.lang.String diagnosticMessage)
In the event of provider failure, set the failure code and a diagnostic message. If this is called on a results set, the OneBox request will be deemed unsuccessful and results will not appear in the end user's search results.

Parameters:
failureCode - the code defining the nature of the failure
diagnosticMessage - descriptive text explaining the failure

setProviderText

public void setProviderText(java.lang.String providerText)
Text identifying the provider that ultimately handled the OneBox request.

setResultsTitleLink

public void setResultsTitleLink(java.lang.String text,
                                java.lang.String url)
Optionally provide a title link for the results set. The link would be a URL to a full result set and the text would be a display description for that link.

setImageUrl

public void setImageUrl(java.lang.String imageUrl)
Optionally provide an identifying icon for the result set. This is the URL path to an image.

addResult

public void addResult(ModuleResult result)
Add an actual result to the OneBox provider's result set. Up to eight results can be returned.

Throws:
java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - when too many results are added

canAddResult

public boolean canAddResult()
Determines whether there is room to add another result. If this returns true the next call to addResult() will succeed.

serialize

public java.lang.String serialize()
Serialize the current state of this OneBoxResults object to an XML string that conforms to the Google Schema for OneBox for Enterprise provider responses.
